Adelani Adepegba, Abuja The Federal Capital Territory Police Command has said candidates, who apply for the 7th regular course of admission into the Nigeria Police Academy, Wudil, Kano, will sit for the entrance examinations on Saturday. It said the exams would hold at the National University Commission auditorium, Maitama and Government Girls Secondary School, Dutse-Alhaji. The FCT police spokesman, DSP Anjuguri Manzah, said in a statement in Abuja on Thursday that candidates should report to their respective centres as indicated on their examination card. He stated, “Candidates initially slated to take the examination at Raw Materials Research and Development Council are now to write their examination at Government Girls Secondary School, Dutse Alhaji.” Copyright PUNCH.
